cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about Chinese Word Segmentation (CWS) using neural networks, which falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT), which is a popular deep learning model for NLP tasks, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions optimization techniques such as model pruning, quantization, and compiler optimization, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories.
